voice_to_text: I know how big of a moment it would be to let Ariana Grande out in the original Juno dress especially knowing that it inspired  Glenda's original bubble dress on Broadway but we're never gonna see it happen maybe they'll allow her out in the original bubble dress but they're never gonna let her out in Juno because Juno is one of the most revered pieces in fashion history it is considered one of Christian Diors greatest masterpieces along with its sister dress Venus and right now it is so old that we don't have the proper technology to be able  to preserve it properly the MET currently cleans it as little as possible because even just moving a single petal for cleaning causes irrevocable sequence loss on it these sequence are also so old now  that they are now sensitive to temperature it needs to be in a temperature controlled environment at all times so that the sequence don't get irrevocably damaged and so that the threads don't decay even more than they already are letting someone out moving in the dress for an entire night would cause damage  similar to the Kim K dress  and unlike the Marilyn Monroe dress and the museum that lent it out to Kim K that obviously did not care about conserving fashion history the Juno dress is owned by the Metropolitan Museum of art maybe they'll recreate it for her like they did with Natalie Portman a couple years ago and I think that Natalie Portman's recreation can definitely  be touched upon and done a lot better  especially for something as big as wicked but they're never gonna let her out in the original dress and it is better that it stays that way
